A Victoria Police spokesperson told Daily Mail Australia the driver had been released from custody overnight 'pending further inquiries'.

Leading Senior Constable Paul Turner told The Age it appeared the boy had ridden out in front of the oncoming car.

Photos from the scene at Plenty River Drive show the boy's green bike crumpled on the side of the road after he was hit at about 8pm.

One local resident, Jess Soltan, who heard helicopter take the boy to hospital said the child was hit   just under the bridge on the road.

